  <summary>5/15/2002--Introduced.
Constitutional Amendment - Declares that marriage in the United States shall consist only of the union of a man and a woman.States that neither this Constitution or the constitution of any State, nor State or federal law, shall be construed to require that marital status or the legal incidents thereof be conferred upon unmarried couples or groups.</summary>
